France will provide military support to the UAE to protect their airspace against any intrusion, the French Armed Forces Minister Florence Parly said on Friday. The French minister said that Rafale combat aircraft, which belong to France’s permanent organization based in Abu Dhabi, are engaged alongside the UAE armed forces in surveillance, detection and interception missions when necessary. Des avions de combat Rafale, qui appartiennent à notre dispositif permanent basé à Abou Dabi, sont ainsi engagés aux côtés des forces armées émiriennes dans des missions de surveillance, de détection et d’interception en cas de besoin. pic.twitter.com/Zvy61yTr4M — Florence Parly (@florence_parly) February 4, 2022  The announcement came in light of the recent Houthi attack on Abu Dhabi that killed 6. On Jan. 17. The Houthis also attempted to attack the UAE last week during Israel’s President, Isaac Herzog’s visit.